{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~kobsa/courses/ICS104/course-notes/1stlevelheaders/elements-of-HCI.htm", "content": "<html>\r<head>\r<title>Elements of HCI</title>\r<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=iso-8859-1\">\r</head>\r\r<body bgcolor=\"#99CCFF\">\r<p><font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=\"6\"><b><font size=\"+6\">Elements \rof HCI</font></b></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><font size=\"5\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">1. \rWhat are user interfaces? </font><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"../what-are-ifs.htm\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\"></a></font></p>\r<p><font size=\"5\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">2. \rUsers are different, usage environments are different </font><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"../users-are-diff.htm\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\"></a></font></p>\r<p><font size=\"5\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">3. \rFactors in HCI </font><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"../factors-in-hci.htm\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The image shows the factors that are taken into account when HCI is construed very broadly: central are user and interface factors, sourrounded by heald and safety factors, organizational factors, comfort factors, task factors, practical constraints,...\"></a></font></p><p><font size=\"5\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">4. \rLevels of analysis </font><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"../levels-of-analysis.htm\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The image shows different levels of analysis in HCI: on Level 1, people and technology are studied. On Level 2, work and immediate environment. On level 3, the social system, organizational goal and technical system\"></a></font></p><p><font size=\"5\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">5. \rMeasurable human factors </font><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"../measurable-factors.htm\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\"></a></font><font size=\"5\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"> \r</font></p><p><font size=\"5\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">6. Disciplines \rcontributing to HCI </font><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"../contr-disciplines.htm\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\"></a></font></p><p><font size=\"5\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">7. \rIntegration of usability testing into the software development process </font><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"../waterfall.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The image shows a traditional waterfall model for software development, with evaluation probably coming at the end.\"></a> \r<a href=\"../star-lifecycle.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The picture shows the star life cycle for software development, with Evaluation being in the center and Prototyping, Implementation, Task Analysis/functional analysis, requirements specifications and conceptual design being linked around with double arrow\"></a> \r</font></p><table width=\"83%\" border=\"0\"> <tr> <td><a href=\"why-learn-about-HCI.htm\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Navigation%20Button%20purple/Navpurp-prev-transp.gif\" width=\"80\" height=\"38\" border=\"0\"></a></td><td> \r<div align=\"right\"><a href=\"cognitive-elements.htm\"><img src=\"../../../../Graphics%20Templates/Navigation%20Button%20purple/Navpurp-next-transparent.gif\" width=\"80\" height=\"38\" border=\"0\"></a></div></td></tr> \r</table><p>&nbsp;</p><p align=\"right\">&nbsp; </p>\r</body>\r</html>\r", "encoding": "ascii"}